<p>Is there a way to write different method implementations for different parameters? Something like this:</p>  <pre><code>class Foo     def some_method("lorem")         true     end     def some_method("ipsum")         false     end end  a = Foo.new a.some_method("lorem") =&gt; true a.some_method("ipsum") =&gt; false </code></pre>  <p>Something similar to Haskell pattern matching</p>